text: Ironton Lodge Hall, also known as Star of the West Lodge, No. 133,A. F. & A. M. Building; and Iron Lodge No. 107. I.O.O.F., is a historic lodge hall located at Ironton, Iron County, Missouri. It was built in 1873, and is a three-story, rectangular brick building with Italianate and Greek Revival style design elements. It measures 29 feet by 57 feet. It was built to serve primarily as a meeting place for fraternal lodges. (includes 8 photographs from 2012) It has served as a Masonic lodge building and as an IOOF hall. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2013. ==References== Category:Clubhouses on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Masonic buildings in Missouri Category:Odd Fellows buildings in Missouri Category:Italianate architecture in Missouri Category:Greek Revival architecture in Missouri Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1873 Category:Buildings and structures in Iron County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Iron County, Missouri Category:1873 establishments in Missouri
